	<div class="intro-section">
		<p class="lead">When planning a wood fence for your Stockton home, two popular styles dominate the conversation: the classic solid privacy fence and the versatile shadow box (also called board-on-board) fence. Each offers distinct advantages depending on your priorities for privacy, airflow, aesthetics, and budget. This guide helps you make the right choice for your specific situation.</p>
	</div>

	<h2>Understanding the Difference</h2>

	<h3>Solid Privacy Fence</h3>
	<p>A solid privacy fence features boards placed edge-to-edge on one side of the rails, creating a continuous barrier with no gaps. This traditional design offers maximum privacy and visual screening.</p>

	<h3>Shadow Box Fence (Board-on-Board)</h3>
	<p>A shadow box fence alternates boards on opposite sides of the rails, with each board partially overlapping the gaps between boards on the other side. This creates a fence that looks finished from both sides while allowing some airflow and filtered visibility.</p>

	<h2>Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>

	<table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 20px 0;">
